---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms & Conditions - OPTYP" 
  description="Detailed Terms and Conditions outlining the rights, responsibilities, and service policies for OPTYP’s professional resume and profile optimization services.">

  <section class="relative py-20 px-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-black via-gray-900 to-black text-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl font-body">

      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-4 text-white">Terms & Conditions</h1>
        <div class="w-20 h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-400 to-green-500 mx-auto mb-8 rounded-full shadow-sm"></div>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          By using OPTYP services, you agree to the following terms and conditions. Please read these terms carefully before using or purchasing our services.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-400">
          Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Content -->
      <article class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none space-y-12 text-gray-300">

        <!-- Service Agreement -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">1. Service Agreement</h2>
          <div class="glass-box p-6 rounded-xl">
            <p>
              By engaging OPTYP’s services, you enter into a binding agreement for professional resume, LinkedIn, and portfolio optimization services as outlined in your selected plan.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-4 space-y-2">
              <li>Services include resume writing, LinkedIn profile optimization, portfolio creation, and related professional branding support.</li>
              <li>Service timelines are detailed in your chosen package.</li>
              <li>All services are delivered digitally unless otherwise specified.</li>
              <li>OPTYP reserves the right to modify or discontinue services with due notice.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Client Responsibilities -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">2. Client Responsibilities</h2>
          <p class="font-semibold mb-4">Clients must ensure:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Providing accurate and up-to-date career and personal details.</li>
            <li>Timely responses to information or feedback requests.</li>
            <li>Reviewing drafts and providing feedback within defined timeframes.</li>
            <li>Respectful communication and professional collaboration.</li>
            <li>Use of delivered content solely for lawful and personal purposes.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Payment Terms -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">3. Payment Terms</h2>
          <div class="glass-box p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-500/40">
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>All payments must be completed before service commencement.</li>
              <li>Prices are listed in INR (₹) and subject to change without prior notice.</li>
              <li>Accepted payment methods include credit/debit cards, UPI, and digital wallets.</li>
              <li>Payments are non-refundable unless explicitly stated in the <a href="/refund/" class="text-teal-300 hover:underline">Refund Policy</a>.</li>
              <li>Service suspension applies in case of non-payment or chargeback initiation.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Service Scope -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">4. Service Scope & Modifications</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Minor revisions are provided as part of every service package.</li>
            <li>Major revisions or additional features may incur additional charges.</li>
            <li>OPTYP reserves the right to decline requests outside the original service scope.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Intellectual Property -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">5. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="glass-box p-4 rounded-lg border border-yellow-500/40">
              <p class="font-semibold text-yellow-300">Ownership of Work</p>
              <p>Upon full payment, ownership of the final deliverables transfers to you. OPTYP retains rights over templates, frameworks, and creative methodologies.</p>
            </div>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Clients may use deliverables solely for professional and personal branding.</li>
              <li>Reselling or distributing OPTYP’s proprietary materials is strictly prohibited.</li>
              <li>OPTYP retains rights to showcase anonymized samples for portfolio purposes.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Service Guarantees -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">6. Service Guarantees & Limitations</h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="glass-box p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-500/40">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-300 mb-3">What We Guarantee</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-sm">
                <li>ATS-friendly resume formatting</li>
                <li>Professional presentation and content optimization</li>
                <li>revisions are based on the service plans</li>
                <li>On-time project delivery as per scope</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="glass-box p-6 rounded-xl border border-red-500/40">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-300 mb-3">What We Cannot Guarantee</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-sm">
                <li>Job interviews or employment results</li>
                <li>External recruiter responses</li>
                <li>Results influenced by third-party actions</li>
                <li>100% compatibility with every ATS platform</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Limitation of Liability -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <div class="glass-box p-6 rounded-xl">
            <p>OPTYP’s total liability shall not exceed the amount paid for the service in question.</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3">
              <li>OPTYP shall not be liable for any indirect, consequential, or incidental damages.</li>
              <li>We are not responsible for losses caused by third-party services or external factors.</li>
              <li>No guarantee is made regarding job outcomes or recruiter responses.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Confidentiality -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">8. Confidentiality</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>All personal data is used strictly for service delivery purposes.</li>
            <li>We maintain confidentiality for all client-provided materials.</li>
            <li>OPTYP employees are bound by confidentiality agreements.</li>
            <li>We comply with applicable data protection laws including GDPR & IT Act 2000.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Force Majeure -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">9. Force Majeure</h2>
          <p>
            OPTYP shall not be held responsible for any failure or delay in performance resulting from events beyond our control, 
            including natural disasters, technical failures, cyber incidents, or regulatory actions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Non-Solicitation -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">10. Non-Solicitation & Fair Use</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Clients may not directly solicit OPTYP’s staff or contractors for private projects.</li>
            <li>Use of services for unlawful, defamatory, or misleading purposes is prohibited.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Dispute Resolution -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">11. Dispute Resolution</h2>
          <p>
            Any dispute arising out of these terms shall first attempt resolution through mediation. 
            If unresolved, it will proceed to binding arbitration under Indian Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Amendments & Severability -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">12. Amendments & Severability</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>OPTYP reserves the right to modify these Terms without prior notice.</li>
            <li>Continued use of the website or services constitutes acceptance of updated terms.</li>
            <li>If any provision is deemed unenforceable, the remaining terms shall remain in effect.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Governing Law -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-teal-400 font-bold text-2xl mb-4">13. Governing Law & Jurisdiction</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <strong>India</strong>. 
            Jurisdiction shall exclusively rest with the courts of <strong>Hyderabad, Telangana</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-500 to-green-500 text-white p-8 rounded-xl text-center shadow-xl">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Questions About Our Terms?</h2>
          <p class="mb-6">For any clarification or dispute-related queries, please contact our legal support team.</p>
          <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@optyp.com" class="underline hover:text-gray-200">info@optyp.com</a></p>
          <p><strong>Contact Page:</strong> <a href="/contact/" class="underline hover:text-gray-200">Visit Our Contact Page</a></p>
        </section>

      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- JSON-LD Structured Data -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "TermsOfService",
    "name": "OPTYP Terms & Conditions",
    "url": "https://optyp.github.io/terms/",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "OPTYP",
      "url": "https://optyp.github.io",
      "contactPoint": {
        "@type": "ContactPoint",
        "email": "info@optyp.com",
        "contactType": "customer support",
        "availableLanguage": ["English"]
      }
    },
    "inLanguage": "en",
    "jurisdiction": "IN",
    "description": "Comprehensive Terms and Conditions for OPTYP, covering service usage, payments, intellectual property, and legal responsibilities."
  }
  </script>

  <style>
    .glass-box {
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
      border: 1px solid rgba(20,184,166,0.4);
      border-radius: 1rem;
      backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
      box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
    }
    article a {
      color: #5eead4;
      transition: color 0.3s ease;
    }
    article a:hover {
      color: #86efac;
    }
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      * {
        animation-duration: 0ms !important;
        transition-duration: 0ms !important;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
